properties.areaDesc: Mountains Of San Benito County And Interior Monterey County Including Pinnacles National Park; Southern Salinas Valley/Arroyo Seco and Lake San Antonio; Santa Lucia Mountains and Los Padres National Forest
properties.headline: Freeze Warning issued February 4 at 8:52AM PST until February 5 at 9:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as 30 expected.

* WHERE...Southern Salinas Valley/Arroyo Seco and Lake San
Antonio, Santa Lucia Mountains and Los Padres National Forest
and Mountains Of San Benito County and Interior Monterey
County Including Pinnacles National Park.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 9 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions will kill crops, other
sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected outdoor
plumbing.
properties.instruction:
Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold. To prevent
freezing and possible bursting of outdoor water pipes they should
be wrapped, drained, or allowed to drip slowly. Those that have
in-ground sprinkler systems should drain them and cover above-
ground pipes to protect them from freezing.

NWSheadline: FREEZE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 AM PST WEDNESDAY
